#. <section class="sutta" id="sn22.78"><article><div class="hgroup"><p class="division">
msgctxt "sn22.78:0.1"
msgid "Saṃyutta Nikāya 22"
msgstr "Linked Discourses 22"

#. </p><p>
msgctxt "sn22.78:0.2"
msgid "8. Khajjanīyavagga"
msgstr "8. Itchy"

#. </p><h1>
#. VAR: 78. Sīhasutta → sīhopamasuttaṃ (bj)
msgctxt "sn22.78:0.3"
msgid "78. Sīhasutta"
msgstr "78. The Lion"

#. </h1></div><p>
#. <a class="pts-vp-pli" id="pts-vp-pli3.85"></a>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc1"></a>
msgctxt "sn22.78:1.1"
msgid "Sāvatthinidānaṃ."
msgstr "At Sāvatthī."

msgctxt "sn22.78:1.2"
msgid ""
"“Sīho, bhikkhave, migarājā sāyanhasamayaṃ āsayā nikkhamati; āsayā "
"nikkhamitvā vijambhati; vijambhitvā samantā catuddisā anuviloketi; samantā "
"catuddisā anuviloketvā tikkhattuṃ sīhanādaṃ nadati; tikkhattuṃ sīhanādaṃ "
"naditvā gocarāya pakkamati."
msgstr ""
"“Mendicants, towards evening the lion, king of beasts, emerges from his den, "
"yawns, looks all around the four directions, and roars his lion’s roar three "
"times. Then he sets out on the hunt."

msgctxt "sn22.78:1.3"
msgid ""
"Ye hi keci, bhikkhave, tiracchānagatā pāṇā sīhassa migarañño nadato saddaṃ "
"suṇanti; yebhuyyena bhayaṃ saṃvegaṃ santāsaṃ āpajjanti; bilaṃ bilāsayā "
"pavisanti; dakaṃ dakāsayā pavisanti; vanaṃ vanāsayā pavisanti; ākāsaṃ "
"pakkhino bhajanti."
msgstr ""
"And the animals who hear the roar of the lion, king of beasts, are typically "
"filled with fear, awe, and terror. They return to their lairs, be they in a "
"hole, the water, or a wood; and the birds take to the air."

#. VAR: cajamānā → mocantā (pts1, mr)
msgctxt "sn22.78:1.4"
msgid ""
"Yepi te, bhikkhave, rañño nāgā gāmanigamarājadhānīsu, daḷhehi varattehi "
"baddhā, tepi tāni bandhanāni sañchinditvā sampadāletvā bhītā muttakarīsaṃ "
"cajamānā, yena vā tena vā palāyanti."
msgstr ""
"Even the royal elephants, bound with strong harness in the villages, towns, "
"and capital cities, break apart their bonds, and urinate and defecate in "
"terror as they flee here and there."

msgctxt "sn22.78:1.5"
msgid ""
"Evaṃ mahiddhiko kho, bhikkhave, sīho migarājā tiracchānagatānaṃ pāṇānaṃ, "
"evaṃ mahesakkho, evaṃ mahānubhāvo."
msgstr ""
"That’s how powerful is the lion, king of beasts, among animals, how "
"illustrious and mighty."

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc2"></a>
msgctxt "sn22.78:2.1"
msgid ""
"Evameva kho, bhikkhave, yadā tathāgato loke uppajjati arahaṃ sammāsambuddho "
"vijjācaraṇasampanno sugato lokavidū anuttaro purisadammasārathi satthā "
"devamanussānaṃ buddho bhagavā. So dhammaṃ deseti:"
msgstr ""
"In the same way, when a Realized One arises in the world—perfected, a fully "
"awakened Buddha, accomplished in knowledge and conduct, holy, knower of the "
"world, supreme guide for those who wish to train, teacher of gods and "
"humans, awakened, blessed—he teaches the Dhamma:"

msgctxt "sn22.78:2.2"
msgid "‘iti rūpaṃ, iti rūpassa samudayo, iti rūpassa atthaṅgamo;"
msgstr "‘Such is form, such is the origin of form, such is the ending of form."

msgctxt "sn22.78:2.3"
msgid "iti vedanā …"
msgstr "Such is feeling …"

msgctxt "sn22.78:2.4"
msgid "iti saññā …"
msgstr "Such is perception …"

msgctxt "sn22.78:2.5"
msgid "iti saṅkhārā …"
msgstr "Such are choices …"

msgctxt "sn22.78:2.6"
msgid "iti viññāṇaṃ, iti viññāṇassa samudayo, iti viññāṇassa atthaṅgamo’ti."
msgstr ""
"Such is consciousness, such is the origin of consciousness, such is the "
"ending of consciousness.’"

msgctxt "sn22.78:2.7"
msgid ""
"Yepi te, bhikkhave, devā dīghāyukā vaṇṇavanto sukhabahulā uccesu vimānesu "
"ciraṭṭhitikā tepi tathāgatassa dhammadesanaṃ sutvā yebhuyyena bhayaṃ "
"saṃvegaṃ santāsaṃ āpajjanti:"
msgstr ""
"Now, there are gods who are long-lived, beautiful, and very happy, living "
"for ages in their divine palaces. When they hear this teaching by the "
"Realized One, they’re typically filled with fear, awe, and terror."

msgctxt "sn22.78:2.8"
msgid "‘aniccāva kira, bho, mayaṃ samānā niccamhāti amaññimha."
msgstr ""
"‘Oh no! It turns out we’re impermanent, though we thought we were permanent!"

msgctxt "sn22.78:2.9"
msgid "Addhuvāva kira, bho, mayaṃ samānā dhuvamhāti amaññimha."
msgstr "It turns out we don’t last, though we thought we were everlasting!"

msgctxt "sn22.78:2.10"
msgid "Asassatāva kira, bho, mayaṃ samānā sassatamhāti amaññimha."
msgstr "It turns out we’re short-lived, though we thought we were eternal!"

msgctxt "sn22.78:2.11"
msgid "Mayampi kira, bho, aniccā addhuvā asassatā sakkāyapariyāpannā’ti."
msgstr ""
"It turns out that we’re impermanent, not lasting, short-lived, and included "
"within identity.’"

msgctxt "sn22.78:2.12"
msgid ""
"Evaṃ mahiddhiko kho, bhikkhave, tathāgato sadevakassa lokassa, evaṃ "
"mahesakkho, evaṃ mahānubhāvo”ti."
msgstr ""
"That’s how powerful is the Realized One in the world with its gods, how "
"illustrious and mighty.”"

msgctxt "sn22.78:2.13"
msgid "Idamavoca bhagavā … pe …"
msgstr "That is what the Buddha said."

msgctxt "sn22.78:2.14"
msgid "etadavoca satthā:"
msgstr "Then the Holy One, the Teacher, went on to say:"

#. </p><blockquote class="gatha"><p>
#. <a class="pts-vp-pli" id="pts-vp-pli3.86"></a>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc3"></a>
msgctxt "sn22.78:3.1"
msgid "“Yadā buddho abhiññāya,"
msgstr "“The Buddha, the teacher without a peer"

#. <br>
msgctxt "sn22.78:3.2"
msgid "dhammacakkaṃ pavattayi;"
msgstr "in all the world with its gods,"

#. <br>
msgctxt "sn22.78:3.3"
msgid "Sadevakassa lokassa,"
msgstr "rolls forth the Wheel of Dhamma"

#. <br>
msgctxt "sn22.78:3.4"
msgid "satthā appaṭipuggalo."
msgstr "from his own insight:"

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc4"></a>
msgctxt "sn22.78:4.1"
msgid "Sakkāyañca nirodhañca,"
msgstr "identity, its cessation,"

#. <br>
msgctxt "sn22.78:4.2"
msgid "sakkāyassa ca sambhavaṃ;"
msgstr "the origin of identity,"

#. <br>
msgctxt "sn22.78:4.3"
msgid "Ariyañcaṭṭhaṅgikaṃ maggaṃ,"
msgstr "and the noble eightfold path"

#. <br>
msgctxt "sn22.78:4.4"
msgid "dukkhūpasamagāminaṃ."
msgstr "that leads to the stilling of suffering."

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc5"></a>
msgctxt "sn22.78:5.1"
msgid "Yepi dīghāyukā devā,"
msgstr "And then the long-lived gods,"

#. <br>
msgctxt "sn22.78:5.2"
msgid "vaṇṇavanto yasassino;"
msgstr "so beautiful and glorious,"

#. <br>
msgctxt "sn22.78:5.3"
msgid "Bhītā santāsamāpāduṃ,"
msgstr "are afraid and full of terror,"

#. <br>
msgctxt "sn22.78:5.4"
msgid "sīhassevitare migā."
msgstr "like the other beasts when they hear a lion."

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc6"></a>
msgctxt "sn22.78:6.1"
msgid "Avītivattā sakkāyaṃ,"
msgstr "‘We haven’t transcended identity!"

#. <br>
msgctxt "sn22.78:6.2"
msgid "aniccā kira bho mayaṃ;"
msgstr "It turns out we’re impermanent!’"

#. <br>
msgctxt "sn22.78:6.3"
msgid "Sutvā arahato vākyaṃ,"
msgstr "So they say when they hear the word"

#. <br>
msgctxt "sn22.78:6.4"
msgid "vippamuttassa tādino”ti."
msgstr "of the perfected one, free and poised.”"

#. </p></blockquote><p class="endsection">
msgctxt "sn22.78:6.5"
msgid "Chaṭṭhaṃ."
msgstr ""
